26s.title: "It wasn't obvious to me in ..."
26s.text: It wasn't obvious to me in the UI whether, if I wanted to give feedback and then continue on to the next linked path, I was supposed to answer the questions and then click the "click here to start on a path to learn them" link, or answer the questions and click the "YES, I GOT THIS" button and then click the new path link, or whether neither would work and I needed to open the new path in a new tab and only then click the "YES, I GOT THIS" button to submit my feedback and move on to yet another page. (It was the second; unknown whether the first would have dropped my feedback.)
